{"lora": {"id": null, "path": null, "strength": 1.0, "signed_url": null}, "seed": 962596, "model": "text-to-video", "prompt": {"enhanced": "A handheld medium shot in the middle of a dense Brazilian jungle at midday, sunlight cutting through thick leaves. The camera shakes slightly as if filmed by another explorer. In the center of frame, a golden lion tamarin monkey with realistic fur stands upright, dressed in a khaki explorer vest with stuffed pockets and a red bandana tied around his head. A rope belt dangles unevenly at his waist, and he carries a pair of oversized binoculars that swing wildly on his chest.

At first, he strikes a heroic pose, puffing out his chest and pointing dramatically toward the treeline as if announcing a discovery. Just as he lifts his foot to march forward, he trips over a gnarled root. He stumbles in slow, exaggerated fashion, arms flailing, barely catching himself on a nearby tree. The binoculars smack into his chest with a loud thud. He freezes for a moment, wide-eyed, scanning around nervously as if checking whether anyone saw him. Then he dusts himself off and pretends it never happened, forcing an overly confident grin and adjusting his vest.

Bird calls echo in the distance, leaves rustle, and faint jungle ambience fills the background. The comedic beat is entirely visual, with the monkey’s over-the-top body language and expressive face carrying the humor.", "original": "A handheld medium shot in the middle of a dense Brazilian jungle at midday, sunlight cutting through thick leaves. Scene 1 — Arrival

Wide panoramic shot: The camera glides over dark blue waters, slowly approaching a rugged shoreline. Waves crash, seabirds cry, towering trees cover the island’s interior.

Sound: Gentle waves, bird calls, whispers of wind through leaves.


---

Scene 2 — The Protagonist

Medium shot → Close-up: We see Raoh, a man resembling an ape — primitive, muscular, his body partly covered in hair, his face showing early human traits. He sits on a rock, watching a group of monkeys working near the jungle edge.

Camera movement: Slow pan left to reveal the monkeys leaping between branches with skill.

Sound: Rustling leaves, monkey chatter, distant jungle calls.

Raoh’s behavior: His eyes burn with curiosity. He mimics their movements, learning silently.


---

Scene 3 — Observation and Learning

Quick cuts:

Close-up of Raoh’s hand grasping a stick.

Feet trying to balance on a log.

Music: Soft rhythm begins, growing with his concentration.

---

Scene 4 — Crafting the Spear

Setting: Deep in the forest, beneath a massive tree.

Medium shot: Raoh selects a strong, straight branch.
Close-up: His hands scrape the bark with a sharp stone, carving a deadly tip. He ties fibers from vines around the shaft for grip.

Sound effects: Stone scraping wood, heavy breaths, rustling foliage.

---

Scene 6 — Celebration

Medium shot: Raoh shares the prey with the monkeys. Younger ones touch the spear curiously. The elder monkey places a hand on Raoh’s shoulder — acceptance into the tribe.

Optional whisper (inner voice): “I belong here.”

Camera: Slow pan upward, showing man and monkeys united under the forest canopy.

Music: Uplifting, warm, symbolizing harmony.


---

Scene 7 — Sunset Ending

Wide panoramic shot: Golden sunlight stretches across the sand as Raoh and the monkeys disappear into the jungle carrying their prize.

Fade out: Text on screen (optional):

> “On this island, survival is not just about strength, but about learning the language of nature.”




---

🎬 Notes for production

Style: Realistic, natural light, balancing wide landscape shots with intimate close-ups.

---
